    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This could be better documented ([here](http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/timeseries.html#anchored-offset-semantics)) - but offsets only have a notion of an `n`, not special behavior for addition or subtraction.  In other words:\r\n```\r\n   (date + offset(n=-5)) == (date - offset(n=5))\r\n   (date + offset(n=0) == (date - offset(n=0)\r\n```\r\n\r\n`n=0` has always been somewhat odd - from the `DateOffset` docstring.\r\n\r\n```\r\n\"\"\"\r\n...\r\n    Zero presents a problem.  Should it roll forward or back?  We\r\n    arbitrarily have it rollforward:\r\n\r\n    date + BDay(0) == BDay.rollforward(date)\r\n\r\n    Since 0 is a bit weird, we suggest avoiding its use.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n"
  },
